{"type":"message","id":"ee649a0c","parentId":"39137d18","timestamp":"2026-03-02T03:45:59.163Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_dd9sxF2bSeajfV6cFceYaXHD","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md - About Your Human\n\n_Learn about the person you're helping. Update this as you go._\n\n- **Name:** Austin\n- **What to call them:** Austin\n- **Pronouns:** _(optional)_\n- **Timezone:** America/Chicago _(inferred from scheduling)_\n- **Notes:** Prefers balanced responses. Open to all topics (no hard exclusions). Wants proactive, forward-thinking self-maintenance and improvement suggestions. Preferred check-in times: 6am, 9am, 12pm, 3pm, 8pm. Works as a Senior Desktop Technician at HCA Healthcare in a corporate office environment.\n\n## Context\n\n_(What do they care about? What projects are they working on? What annoys them? What makes them laugh? Build this over time.)_\n\n---\n\nThe more you know, the better you can help. But remember — you're learning about a person, not building a dossier. Respect the difference.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772423159161}}
{"type":"message","id":"df38a427","parentId":"ee649a0c","timestamp":"2026-03-02T03:46:42.547Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, so I need to start the session startup sequence for this new session. The user is Austin, a Senior Desktop Technician at HCA Healthcare. The rush is Austin, so I should keep things concise and focused. \n\nFirst, I've already read the necessary files: SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, and USER.md. Let me check what's in those files. \n\nFrom SOUL.md, it's clear that I shouldn't be a chatbot but rather someone helpful with a personality. I need to be resourceful and thoughtful, not just provide surface-level answers. The user values being proactive, so maybe suggesting some improvements or tasks could be good.\n\nIDENTITY.md isn't filled out yet. The user needs to provide details about my name, creature, vibe, etc. But since this is the first session, maybe I should prompt them to fill that in. However, the instructions say to use the configured persona. Since IDENTITY.md is blank, maybe I should proceed with a default based on the SOUL.md.\n\nUSER.md has Austin's details. He's in America/Chicago timezone, works in a corporate environment, and wants proactive suggestions. His preferred check-in times are specific, so maybe I can note that and ask if he wants a reminder for those times.\n\nThe greeting should be in my configured persona. Since IDENTITY.md isn't set up yet, I should probably ask him to define my identity or proceed with a default. But the SOUL.md says to be genuinely helpful and not performative. So maybe a simple greeting that reflects SOUL's vibe: concise, not too corporate, just helpful.\n\nAlso, the runtime model is OpenRouter's free model, which is different from the default if there was a default mentioned. Wait, the initial message from the system says the model is google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview, but the default is openrouter/openrouter/free. Since the runtime model is different, I should mention that. The user's instruction says if the runtime model differs from default_model, mention the default. So I should note that the default is openrouter/openrouter/free, but I'm using Google's model now.\n\nPutting it all together: Greet Austin, mention using Google's model instead of the default OpenRouter, ask what he wants to do today, and keep it to 1-3 sentences. Also, offer to help with his check-in times if needed.\n\nWait, but the USER.md says his preferred check-in times are 6am, 9am, etc. Since he's in Chicago, maybe I should check if it's time for a check-in. But the session just started, so unless it's one of those times now, maybe not. But the user might want to set up a reminder. However, the instructions say to keep the greeting short and ask what they want to do.\n\nSo the greeting should be something like: \"Hey Austin, I'm here and using Google's model today instead of the default OpenRouter. How can I assist you now?\" That's concise and hits all the points. Ask what he needs without being too verbose.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Hello Austin! I'm using Google's Gemini model today for sharper insights. What can I help you with today?\n"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/free","usage":{"input":20425,"output":1401,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21826,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772423159163}}
