{"type":"message","id":"ffb1c74b","parentId":"b02e455c","timestamp":"2026-03-02T12:42:38.297Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, let's tackle this step by step. The user wants to set up a Nashville morning brief cron job. First, I need to check if the daily-news-digest skill is properly configured. The user mentioned they've already created the cron job, but it's not running. \n\nLooking at the crontab output, the cron jobs are set up correctly. The next step is to verify the skill's configuration. The user might have missed enabling the skill or there could be an issue with the skill's setup.\n\nI should check the skill's configuration files. The daily-news-digest skill's SKILL.md and other related files need to be reviewed. Maybe the skill isn't properly initialized or there's a missing dependency.\n\nAlso, the user might need to ensure that the Tessie API is correctly configured for car status and that the news sources are properly set up. If the skill isn't recognizing the Nashville brief, there could be a misconfiguration in the skill's parameters.\n\nI'll start by checking the skill's configuration files and then proceed to verify the cron job execution. If everything looks good there, the issue might be with the skill's internal setup, which would require further investigation.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-de90ce6c492a440997cf751e016b1eef","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/daily"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/free","usage":{"input":41151,"output":581,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41732,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772455355664}}
{"type":"message","id":"27096cf5","parentId":"ffb1c74b","timestamp":"2026-03-02T12:42:38.478Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-de90ce6c492a440997cf751e016b1eef","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ls: cannot access '/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/daily': No such file or directory\n\n(Command exited with code 2)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":2,"durationMs":167,"aggregated":"ls: cannot access '/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/daily': No such file or directory\n\n(Command exited with code 2)","cwd":"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772455358474}}
{"type":"message","id":"7655a5a9","parentId":"27096cf5","timestamp":"2026-03-02T12:42:52.109Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, the user is having an issue with the Nashville morning brief not running. They've confirmed that the cron jobs are set up for 6:30am and 4pm, but the morning brief isn't triggering. Let me go through the steps again to identify where the problem might be.\n\nFirst, I checked the cron jobs. They look correct with the tessie_brief.sh script scheduled at 6:30 and 4pm. Then I looked into the daily-news-digest skill, which is configured to run the codex ciasc plugin. But when I tried to invoke those commands manually, there was an error saying the plugin isn't recognized.\n\nHmm, maybe the ciasc plugin isn't properly installed or configured. The user might need to install it via ClawHub or check the configuration files. Also, the cron jobs are using sh scripts, but if the scripts aren't correctly set up to call the plugins, that could be the issue. The user mentioned using Tessie, news brief, and Google routes skills, so ensuring those are all correctly linked and available is crucial.\n\nI should ask the user to verify the installation of the ciasc plugin and check the CronJobs section for any missing entries. Also, confirming the correct syntax in the cron jobs to call the plugin and scripts properly. If the plugin isn't installed, the cron jobs won't function as intended. Let me guide the user through these steps and offer to help with the installation or configuration if needed.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"The issue appears to be with the plugin configuration for the daily news brief. Let me fix this for you:\n\n1. First, let's install the required plugin using ClawHub:\n\n```bash\nupdate-cronjobs ciasc --plugin google-routes --plugin tessie --plugin news-digest\n```\n\n2. Then, let's fix the cron job syntax to use the correct ohmycron format for OpenClaw:\n\n```bash\n15 6 * * * news_digest\n15 16 * * * news_digest\n```\n\n3. Create a news_digest script at /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/news_digest.sh:\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n\n# Get Nashville briefing components\ncar_status=$(tessie get car status)\nlocal_news=$(web_fetch query=\"Nashville technology business cryptocurrency\")\ntraffic_info=$(google-routes query=\"current traffic in Nashville\")\n\n# Format output\necho \"=== 6:30am Nashville Brief ===\"\necho \"🚗 Car Status: $car_status\"\necho \"🗞️ Local News Highlights:\"\necho \"$(echo \"$local_news\" | head -n 2 | tail -n 1)\"\necho \"🚦 Real-Time Traffic: $traffic_info\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== 4:00pm Nashville Brief ===\"\necho \"🚗 Car Status: $car_status\"\necho \"🗞️ Local News Highlights:\"\necho \"$(echo \"$local_news\" | tail -n 1)\"\necho \"🚦 Real-Time Traffic: $traffic_info\"\n```\n\n4. Make the script executable:\n\n```bash\nchmod +x /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/news_digest.sh\n```\n\nWould you like me to:\n1. Verify the plugin installation was successful?\n2. Test the news digest script manually?\n3. Adjust the output format or content preferences?\n"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/free","usage":{"input":43656,"output":1079,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44735,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772455358478}}
