{"type":"message","id":"0d12c10c","parentId":"f1300d2a","timestamp":"2026-03-02T14:01:45.249Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to do all three: confirm cron jobs updated, test script execution, and set up notifications for deliveries. I have already added the cron jobs earlier. Now I should:\n\n1. Perform a command to confirm the cron jobs are updated (already have output from `crontab -l` showing them) but I need to output confirmation.\n\n2. Test script execution manually using `exec` command.\n\n3. Set up notifications for deliveries - not sure which tool to use.\n\nFor notification setup, maybe we can use `mail` command or send via internal messaging? There's a `message` tool that can send messages. We could configure notifications by adding email or telegram notifications in the script. Simpler might be to add an echo to file that can be read.\n\nBut we need to follow policy: we can't just send messages without specifying action and target. We can use `message` tool to send a notification. Perhaps we can schedule a notification message at the end of script. Or maybe the script can log and we can monitor logs and send a notification.\n\nI think we can just provide instructions to add notification within the script: e.g., add `echo \"Brief executed\"` to a log file, and we can monitor it.\n\nBut they asked to set up notifications. Using the `message` tool, we could send a Telegram message to a channel when the script runs. However, they'd need to set up channel etc.\n\nSimplify: Add a line in the script to log execution and maybe use `exec` to send a message? Or we can schedule a cron job that sends a notification after script execution.\n\nProbably easiest: We can append a line to the script that sends a Telegram message via `message` tool after execution. But need to call `message` tool.\n\nWe can add at the end of script:\n\n```bash\n# Send notification\nmessage action=send channel=telegram target=telegram:8268094294 message=\"Nashville brief completed at $(date)\"\n```\n\nBut they didn't specify channel usage earlier. Might be okay.\n\nAlternatively just write to log file and they can monitor.\n\nGiven policy, it's safe to add a simple log line.\n\nI'll do:\n\n1. Confirm cron jobs: `crontab -l | grep nashville_brief.sh` output exists.\n\n2. Test script execution: `bash /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/nashville_brief.sh` and show output.\n\n3. Set up notifications: Add a line to log to file and optionally send a message. I can just log to a file.\n\nBetter: Use `write` tool to log successful execution to a status file.\n\nI'll do:\n\n- Append to `/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/nashville_brief_last_run.log` with timestamp.\n\n- Possibly send a Telegram message via `message` tool.\n\nI'll call `message` action send.\n\nWho to send to? Possibly to themselves? There's no target Id given. We can use `message` action=send with channel \"telegram\" and target maybe something like \"telegram:8268094294\" which was earlier chat id.\n\nI'll do that.\n\nProceed:\n\n1. Confirm cron jobs: No need to run a command; just show that they exist.\n\n2. Test script execution: Run script via exec.\n\n3. Set up notification: Add a final line to script to send a Telegram message using `message` tool.\n\nNeed to modify script to include message sending? I could rewrite script now with that addition.\n\nBut script already exists. Let's overwrite it with addition:\n\nAdd at end before `EOL`:\n\nAdd:\n\n```\n# Send completion notification\nmessage action=send channel=telegram target=telegram:8268094294 message=\"✅ Nashville brief executed at $(date +'%H:%M %d/%m/%Y')\"\n```\n\nMake sure quoting correct.\n\nI'll rewrite script.\n\nProceed with exec to overwrite script.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2501e918ac8a45e0821c6f4c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat > /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/nashville_brief.sh <<'EOL'\n#!/bin/bash\n# Nashville Brief Script - 6:30am & 4:00pm\n\n# Get car status via Tessie\ncar_status=$(tessie parse car status 2>&1)\n\n# Get local Nashville news using RSS feeds\nlocal_news=$(curl -s \"https://www.wsch.com/feed/news.rss\" | grep -E '<title>|<item>|<desc>' | head -n 3 | tr -d '\\n' | sed 's/<[^>]*>//g')\n\n# Get Google Routes traffic info\ntraffic_info=$(curl -s \"https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/distancematrix/json?origins=36.1658,-86.7878&destinations=36.1462,-86.7855&key=YOUR_API_KEY&units=imperial\" | jq '.rows[0].elements[0].duration.text')\n\n# Format output\nif [ \"$car_status\" == \"success\" ]; then\n    car_status=\"Online\"\nelse\n    car_status=\"Offline - $car_status\"\nfi\n\necho \"=== 6:30 AM Nashville Brief ===\"\necho \"🚗 Car Status: $car_status\"\necho \"🗞️ Local News Highlights:\"\necho \"$local_news\"\necho \"🚦 Traffic Conditions (Downtown): $traffic_info minutes\"\necho\n\necho \"=== 4:00 PM Nashville Brief ===\"\necho \"🚗 Car Status: $car_status\"\necho \"🗞️ Local News Highlight:\"\necho \"$local_news\" | tail -n 1\necho \"🚦 Traffic Conditions (City): $traffic_info minutes\"\necho\n\n# Send completion notification to Telegram\nmessage action=send channel=telegram target=telegram:8268094294 message=\"✅ Nashville brief executed at $(date +'%H:%M %d/%m/%Y')\"\nEOL"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/free","usage":{"input":64369,"output":2281,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66650,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772460075294}}
