{"type":"message","id":"f4161314","parentId":"e00131da","timestamp":"2026-03-02T16:09:58.596Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, let's tackle this step by step. The user wants to set up a Nashville brief that runs at 6:30 AM and 4:00 PM daily, using Tessie for car status and local news. They also want notifications if the script fails.\n\nFirst, I need to create the script that fetches car status via Tessie and local news. The script should be placed in the workspace tools directory. Let me check the existing files to ensure there's no conflict.\n\nNext, the user wants notifications if the script fails. I'll use the `notify-send` command to send desktop notifications. But wait, the user might not have notifications set up, so I should include a fallback to email or log files.\n\nThen, the Nashville brief needs to include car status, local news, and traffic info. I'll structure the script to pull data from Tessie and local sources, format it nicely, and send notifications.\n\nI should also make sure the script is executable and test it manually. Let me write the script with proper error handling and logging.\n\nFinally, set up the cron jobs for 6:30 AM and 4:00 PM. The user might need to adjust the script to include specific sources or APIs for the news and traffic data. I'll include placeholders for those as well.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-a40ed75de87842829fc07959f41bf588","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat > /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/nashville_brief.sh <<'EOF'\n#!/bin/bash\n\n# Nashville Brief Script - 6:30am & 4:00pm\n\n# Get car status via Tessie\ncar_status=$(tessie parse car status 2>&1)\n\n# Get local news using RSS feeds\nlocal_news=$(curl -s \"https://www.wsch.com/feed/news.rss\" | grep -E '<title>|<item>' | head -n 3)\n\n# Get Google Routes traffic info\ntraffic_info=$(curl -s \"https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/distancematrix/json?origins=3