might need guidance on how to install Tessie correctly or alternative methods to achieve their goal without Tessie.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I've identified the issue - the Tessie CLI isn't properly installed in your environment. Let me help you resolve this step by step:\n\n1. **Install Tessie CLI** (if not already installed):\n```bash\nopenclaw install tessie\n```\n\n2. **Verify Tessie installation**:\n```bash\nwhich tessie\n```\n\n3. **Create the Nashville brief script** with proper Tessie integration:\n```bash\ncat > /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/nashville_brief.sh <<'EOF'\n#!/bin/bash\n# Nashville Brief Script - 6:30am & 4:00pm\n\n# Get car status via Tessie\ncar_status=$(tessie parse car status 2>&1)\n\n# Get local Nashville news using RSS feeds\nlocal_news=$(curl -s \"https://www.wsch.com/feed/news.rss\" | grep -E '<title>|<item>' | head -n 3 | tr -d '\\n')\n\n# Get Google Routes traffic info\ntraffic_info=$(curl -s \"https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/distancematrix/json?origins=36.1658,-86.7878&destinations=36.1462,-86.7855&key=YOUR_API_KEY\" | jq '.rows[0].elements[0].duration.text')\n\n# Format output\necho \"=== 6:30 AM Nashville Brief ===\"\necho \"🚗 Car Status: $car_status\"\necho \"🗞️ Local News Highlights:\"\necho \"$local_news\"\necho \"🚦 Traffic Conditions (Downtown): $traffic_info\"\necho \"=== 4:00 PM Nashville Brief ===\"\necho \"🚗 Car Status: $car_status\"\necho \"🗞️ Local News Highlight:\"\necho \"$local_news\" | tail -n 1\necho \"🚦 Traffic Conditions (City): $traffic_info\"\nEOF\n```\n\n4. **Make the script executable**:\n```bash\nchmod +x /home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/nashville_brief.sh\n```\n\n5. **Test the script**:\n```bash\n/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/tools/nashville_brief.sh\n```\n\nThis should now work correctly. The script will:\n- Get car status via Tessie\n- Fetch local news headlines\n- Provide traffic updates\n- Format output for both morning and afternoon briefings\